      • testStopDefineMixingStep

        public void testStopDefineMixingStep(String message,
                            boolean shouldBeCalled,
                            boolean top,
                            boolean clockwise,
                            int startX,
                            int endX,
                            int startY,
                            double stepSize)
        Tests whether implementation is correct.
        Parameters:
        message - Textual description of the test case.
        shouldBeCalled - Stores whether a new step should be created (and added to the protocol).
        top - Indicates whether the top wall should be moved.
        clockwise - Indicates whether the movement is in clockwise direction.
        startX - Starting x-coordinate when the swipe is initiated.
        startY - Starting y-coordinate when the swipe is initiated.
        endX - Final x-coordinate when the swipe is terminated.
        stepSize - Desired step size for the Step.
